  "prompt": "Can you hard boil eggs in the microwave?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to hard boil eggs in the microwave, but it requires caution to prevent the eggs from exploding due to rapid heating. Here is a method to safely hard boil eggs in the microwave:\n\n1. **Preparation:**\n   - Place the eggs in a microwave-safe bowl.\n   - Add enough water to the bowl to cover the eggs completely. The eggs should be submerged by at least an inch of water.\n   - Add a pinch of salt to the water. This helps to prevent the eggs from bursting.\n\n2. **Cooking:**\n   - Microwave the bowl of water and eggs on high for about 9-12 minutes. The exact time may vary depending on your microwave and the number of eggs you're cooking.\n   - Stop the microwave and check the eggs every few minutes to ensure they do not overcook.\n\n3. **Cooling:**\n   - Once the eggs are cooked, carefully remove the bowl from the microwave (it will be hot).\n   - Transfer the eggs to a bowl of ice water to stop the cooking process and make them easier to handle.\n\n4. **Peeling:**\n   - Peel the eggs once they are cool enough to handle.\n\nAlways be cautious when using a microwave for boiling eggs and follow safety guidelines to prevent accidents.",
